---
title: Cheesy Spinach & Mushroom Stromboli with Pillsbury™ Classic Pizza Crust & Marinara Sauce
description: This Italian-style turnover has everything! Garlicky mushrooms and spinach are sprinkled with Parmesan, then wrapped up in a buttery pizza dough with a blanket of mozzarella. While the outside turns golden and crispy in the oven, fillings melt and meld to form a soft and savory center. Finally, the cheesy stuffed treasures are sliced and dunked in a marinara for an umami punch. Holy stromboli!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/cheesy-spinach-mushroom-stromboli-77dae95a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cheesy-spinach-mushroom-stromboli-63b468d1275b65eec40fedd0-fd89eb64.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-spinach-mushroom-stromboli-63b468d1275b65eec40fedd0
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 24 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1090 mg
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Add another drizzle of oil, then stir in @Spinach{5%ounce} (you may need to add spinach in batches). Cook, stirring, until spinach is slightly wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add garlic and half the @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until spinach is wilted and garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer veggies to a medium #bowl{}; let cool slightly.

While veggies cool, place @Butter{1/2%tablespoon} (1 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave until butter has melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Remove @Pillsbury™ Classic Pizza Crust{7%ounce} from tube and unroll onto a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Slice in half at perforation and use your hands to stretch each piece into a 6-by-8-inch rectangle.

> For 4, fully assemble the first two stromboli before starting on the second two so they all fit on the same baking sheet.

Spread @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup} evenly across each piece of dough, leaving a ½-inch border around edges. Top with veggies (draining first if needed) and @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}.

Gently roll up each dough rectangle, starting with one of the short sides, to form a log. Arrange logs on baking sheet, seam sides down; pinch ends to close and tuck under each log.

Brush stromboli with melted butter; lightly season with salt and pepper. Wash out bowl.

Bake on middle rack until deep golden brown and crisp, ~{14-16%minutes}.

When stromboli are almost done, place @Marinara Cup{5%ounce} in bowl used for butter; cover bowl tightly with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until sauce is warmed through, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Transfer stromboli to a #cutting board{}; slice crosswise into quarters.

Divide between plates. Serve with warm marinara on the side for dipping.